# Claude Code Rules for Portfolio Project

## Stack
- Astro (no React, no TypeScript)
- SCSS only (no Tailwind)
- pnpm as package manager
- Minimal JavaScript (only when necessary for interactivity)

## Code Style
- Use design tokens from src/styles/tokens/
- Modern SCSS with @use and @forward (not @import)
- File-based routing in src/pages/

## Component Conventions
- Every component lives in its own folder under src/components/ComponentName/
- Each component has a matching SCSS file in the same folder: ComponentName.astro + ComponentName.scss
- Both files use PascalCase to match (e.g. Button.astro, Button.scss)
- The SCSS file is imported in the component's frontmatter: import "./ComponentName.scss"
- The SCSS file imports tokens via: @use "../../styles/tokens" as tokens
- Import components using path aliases: import Button from "@components/Button/Button.astro"
- Import styles using path aliases: import "@styles/index.scss"
- Available aliases: @components → src/components, @styles → src/styles, @layouts → src/layouts
- Aliases are defined in astro.config.mjs (build) and tsconfig.json (IDE support)
- SCSS @use also uses absolute paths from src/ root via loadPaths in astro.config.mjs: @use "styles/tokens" as tokens

## Developer Context
- User is proficient in HTML/CSS/SCSS
- User is learning JavaScript - explain JS concepts when introducing them
- User prefers clean, readable code over clever abstractions
- User wants to understand what's happening, not just copy-paste

## Project Goals
- Build a portfolio site to showcase design work
- Learn modern web development workflows
- Understand component architecture via Astro
- Practice Git branching and deployment